    statementOfFactsText: `According to early Seerah accounts, he drew up a written document.
This is a document from Muhammad, the Messenger of Allah, concerning the Emigrants and the Helpers and those who follow them and strive alongside them.
They are one community (ummah) to the exclusion of other people.
The Emigrants of Quraysh remain bound together; they pay blood-money among themselves and ransom their captives in a just and recognized manner.
Every clan among the Helpers remains upon its former structure; each group pays its blood-money and ransoms its captives in a just and recognized manner.
The believers shall not leave any one of them burdened by blood-money or ransom without helping him in a fair manner.
A believer shall not kill another believer on account of a disbeliever, nor shall he support a disbeliever against a believer.
The least of the believers may grant protection on behalf of all, and their protection is to be respected.
The believers are allies and supporters of one another, to the exclusion of other people.
Whoever among the Jews follows the believers and joins their pact shall have help and support; they shall not be wronged, nor shall anyone be aided against them.
The peace (truce) of the believers is one.
No separate peace shall be made while the believers are engaged in battle in the path of Allah.
Any peace must be concluded on the basis of equality and justice between them.
Whoever deliberately kills a believer without right is subject to retaliation (qiṣāṣ), unless the guardian of the slain is pleased to accept blood-money or to pardon.`,
